      • isBetween

        public boolean isBetween(int lower,
                         int upper,
                         boolean inclusive,
                         IntParameter.IsBetweenFailureCallback... errorCallbacks)
        Checks that the internal value of the IntParameter is between the provided lower and upper bound. Whether or not the bounds are included or excluded in the interval, can be controlled using the inclusive parameter. When inclusive is true the internal value of the IntParameter must conform to value >= lower && value <= upper for the check to pass. When inclusive is false the internal value of the IntParameter must conform to value > lower && value < upper for the check to pass.
        Parameters:
        lower - The lower bound which the internal value of the IntParameter must exceed, and may equal depending on the flag provided to the inclusive parameter, for the check to pass.
        upper - The upper bound which the internal value of the IntParameter must not exceed, and may equal depending on the flag provided to the inclusive parameter, for the check to pass.
        errorCallbacks - The error handlers that are notified in case the check fails.
        Returns:
        true if the check passes, false is all other cases.

      • isBetween

        public boolean isBetween(int lower,
                         int upper,
                         IntParameter.IsBetweenFailureCallback... errorCallbacks)
        Checks that the internal value of the IntParameter is between the provided lower and upper bound. The internal value of the IntParameter must conform to value >= lower && value <= upper for the check to pass. If the provided bounds should not be valid, use the isBetween(int, int, boolean, IsBetweenFailureCallback...) method, where the inclusivity setting can be provided as a parameter.
        Parameters:
        lower - The lower bound which the internal value of the IntParameter must exceed or equal for the check to pass.
        upper - The upper bound which the internal value of the IntParameter must not exceed or equal for the check to pass.
        errorCallbacks - The error handlers that are notified in case the check fails.
        Returns:
        true if the check passes, false is all other cases.
        See Also:
        isBetween(int, int, boolean, IsBetweenFailureCallback...)
